    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The relative disposition and way of arrangement of the various parts of the body of a human, or sometimes of an animal. Includes the position and carriage of the limbs, hands, head, or the body as a whole, often as indicating a particular quality or feeling. Examples of displays of body position include in the visual arts, dance, and ritual.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
